---
title: Cherry Ancho Chicken with Pistachio Rice & Roasted Asparagus
description: Chicken paired with a fruit-based sauce is a classic combo. Our chefs decided to take things a step further by adding ancho chili powder to the mix, creating a smoky, sultry mystique to cherry jam and dried tart cherries to pour over succulent, seared chicken cutlets. The excitement continues with the sides: fragrant, pistachio-studded rice and tender roasted asparagus. This is just the sort of dish we want to make when we’re feeling a little fancy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63a0b02ca6ecbce8560c6845-1d249f83.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/cherry-ancho-chicken-63a0b02ca6ecbce8560c6845-e565ca9c.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 79 g
  sugar: 30 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 450 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cherry-ancho-chicken-63a0b02ca6ecbce8560c6845
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook,
stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

While rice cooks, trim and discard bottom 1 inch from @asparagus{6%oz}. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium heat. Add
chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side. Remove pan
from heat.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @cherry jam{1}, @chicken demi-glace{1},
@ancho chili powder{1%tsp}, and @water{1/4%cup}.

Return pan with chicken to low heat; add jam mixture and @dried cherries{1%oz}. Simmer,
turning chicken to evenly coat, until sauce has thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}, leaving sauce in pan.

> TIP: If sauce is too thick, add a splash or two of water.

Heat pan with sauce over low heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat and set aside.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @pistachios{1%oz}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice and asparagus between plates and garnish with scallion greens. Serve chicken
alongside; drizzle with sauce.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.